<Author>Annisobel
<Content>Fantastic stay in a wonderful hotel My husband and I stayed in the MeMadrid hotel from 11th to 15th November 2008 for a preChristmas City Break. We had booked a supreme room on Expedia and joined the Mas Reward scheme beforehand. I emailed the hotel before our break and requested a non-smoking king bed room overlooking Plaza Santa Ana. The room we were allocated was simply superb and had a fantastic view of the Plaza. The bed was very comfortable and the techy equipment and lighting was great fun. The shower room was equally superb with a fantastic shower. The reception desk and concierge were at all times very friendly and helpful. The bar staff, both in the ground floor bar and the rooftop bar were at all times really friendly and good at their jobs. We had absolutly no problems with noise even though our room overlooked the plaza - we slept exceptionally well and heard no noise from the plaza or the rooftop bar. The windows in our room had the original windows overlaid with excellent double glazing windows. The location of this hotel is excellent. On our previous trip to Madrid we had stayed at one of the big hotels on Gran Via but would now always stay in this location. We ate in the restaurant for one breakfast and the food was excellent. The other mornings we ate at a local cafe - we were too full from all the tapas we ate in the evening to justify eating a large breakfast. again. The hotel is walking distance to the 3 great art museums in Madrid and the only time we used the metro was to go to Real Madrid football ground to do the stadium tour. I guess you get what you pay for - if you choose the cheapest rate you will get the smallest room, if you choose a mid rate you will get an excellent room with a great view. By joining the Mas Reward programme we were able to receive two English newspapers for free every morning and to have the buffet breakfast in the restaurant for half price - how great is that. I have recommended this hotel to many friends since our return - if you want to stay in a great hotel in a fantastic location in a fun city like Madrid, this is the place for you. 
