<Author>Holiday_Hunter123
<Content>Hip, happening and great value We stayed at the ME Madrid in August 2008. The hotel is in a great location, really central and in a pleasant square with a number of tapas bars in.We had booked a standard (i.e. deluxe) room, and found it to be really spacious, with a massive bed, flat screen TV, 2 armchairs, coffee table and well stocked minibar. Loved the lighting options too! We had booked on the ME wants you in Madrid package, which meant that there was a bottle of cava with strawberries and dipping chocolate in our room. The bathroom was also huge with a fantastic double shower. Contrary to some of the other reviews, we didn't have a problem with noise at all (We had an internal room with no view but probably the best bet if you prefer quiet at night).Tip - try to get a package which includes breakfast as it is otherwise quite expensive. There are a number of packages available on the hotel's own website and I found these to be similarly priced to supposed discount websites.The restaurant and downstairs bar are fantastic, very hip and trendy but certainly no attitude, and the service was very good.The upstairs bar is great for views (although very windy!), the only frustrating point was that despite going up there early (9pm), all seats were reserved - which doesn't make sense given that there wasn't a queue at that point to sit on them - I think the hotel needs to manage this better.Altogether though, I couldn't recommend the hotel highly enough, it's reasonable value and a stylish place to spend the weekend. 
