<Content>We just loved it We spend 5 nights at ME MAdrid with our Kids ages 9 and 13. We got two connected rooms and they were small but that is what we expected. They were however very comfortable. Great lighting and AC was perfect. We chose to have interior rooms to avoid the noise and the fact that they faced and inside cortyard did not bodered us at all. If you want a bigger room then just pay for it.We signed up to become Melia members and got breakfast for all 4 for 44 Euros instead of 88 every day.The staff was great! Thank you Ivan and Celia. They guided us very well during our stay.The location of this hotel is fantastic. You can walk to the museums, to Plaza Mayor, Palacio Real, Calle Serrano... everywhere. The location is also fun, Plaza Santa Ana is busy and charming.Celia recommended El Lacon for Tapas and it was great, also went to Huevos de Lucio and loved the huevos con patatas. One night the kids stayed in the hotel and we enjoyed an incredible meal at Ramses in Plaza de Alcala! to our surprise we sat next to Pedro Almodobar... Ramses also has a great bar and dancing area, but be aware that the dancing doesn't start til 2:00am. Make reservations in advanced.DO NOT EAT AT ANY OF THE RESTAURANT INSIDE PLAZA MAYOR. Our only bad experience in Madrid was a dinner at one of the places in there, the food was terrible and very expensive. Later we commented our experience with the concierge at ME Madrid and they never recommend it there. The restaurants at the side streets are much better.We did two day trips to Toledo and to Segovia and Avila and they were both incredible. We wished we had stayed a cople of extra days to fully enjoy Me and Madrid! 
