<Content>Hotel - Yes.....Madrid - No! Modern, trendy hotel in a great location to explore the city. We spent New Year's Eve in the Penthouse Bar which has fantastic views over the city..... great music and a great atmosphere and a great crowd! There was a meal on offer but we chose not to bother with this as we arrived quite late. This was after venturing to the Puerta Del Sol and deciding it may not be too clever an idea to stay there! Bit rough!! The hotel staff were welcoming and friendly, very young and very hip ! Special mention to the concierges who provide an excellent helpful service. The rooms are on the small side but i would agree with an earlier review that the bed is nothing short of fantastic. Altho' small the rooms are modern, clean and have all the technology one might need. The bathroom was again modern and well appointed, especially the shower which was fab! All in all the room was most acceptable for the price we paid...which was not the hotel's own website price! Breakfast was the usual; fresh fruit, all types of eggs, bacon, cereal, toast. Pricey at 20.50 euros tho. Service here and in the bar was very good. Security was good also in that the elevators would only operate with the insertion of your room card. Check in and check out were painless even with the added nusiance of the hotel having a booking in our name for two double rooms instead of the three we booked with the website. There was absolutely no fuss made or questions asked and it was dealt with in seconds. Location was excellent, walking distance to Puerta del sol, Gran Via, Prado museum etc....be warned the queues we saw for this on the 2nd January were horrendous!! This was just after 9.00a.m! Plaza Santa Ana is a lovely little square with craft stalls and plenty going on. Altho we would thoroughly recommend the hotel we would not return to Madrid (unless for the hotel's New Year Party!) Not a patch on Barcelona or even Valencia....unfriendly, not too clean, not that much to see and do apart from the museums and shops. We look forward to trying another ME hotel after this experience. 
