<Author>saintba
<Content>ME Madrid Reina Victoria - Flawless 5 Star Experience I just had a 3 night stay in the ME Madrid Reina Victoria hotel. It was great. I'm posting an objective review of the hotel below.My girlfriend had never been to Europe before so for my birthday I decided to treat the both of us to a trip through Europe. I wanted everything to be perfect. I booked each part of my trip myself since I have traveled to Europe many, many times. I was just in Spain a few months ago and I had drinks on top of the outdoor terrace at the hotel and I was really impressed by the hotel and location so I booked it.It was a GREAT experience that was truly flawless. There are 191 hotel rooms here from $350 (with tax) all the way up to $2,000 a night rooms. We stayed in a nice suite that was about $500 a night with taxes and it was great. The room was spacious, the bathroom very high end with marble throughout and the room had a big LCD TV with a DVD player (which we didn't use). The lighting system was great with controls on both sides of the bed to control lighting for the entire room. The mini-bar selection was very good. Also, there was free hi-speed wireless internet and internet with a cord and it was very fast and FREE. I was impressed as we had arrived from Buenos Aires earlier than our check-in and they had everything ready and let us check-in early. Fortunately, we flew first class so we both slept on the plane as there were seats that folded completely flat into beds so we were both ready to explore. Right away the concierge called up and asked me if I needed anything and to let me know that she would be available for anything I needed. Then the manager of the hotel called as well. I'm not sure if this is normal but it was great. Then shortly after their call, they had a nice card welcoming me and they also included both of their business cards as well and let me know if I needed anything they would be available. I thought that was a very nice touch and I was impressed.I'm in the hospitality business and I'm also a real estate developer. I could notice they spent a lot of money on the finish out of the room and they used very good items. The bed was VERY comfortable, the pillows were excellent and the room had black out blinds so we could sleep in. Also, something which was nice was they put sound-proof windows on the windows. I read a review of someone that said it was loud but I can assure you that the room was totally quiet and we didn't hear a thing. The location is PERFECT right in front of Plaza Santa Ana and it's in Central Madrid close to all the museums and not far from all the shopping on Serrano Street. There is a metro station very close as well (Banco de Espana). We ate dinner one night in the restaurant and it was great. We also drank drinks on the terrace and it's a really cool place. The staff was great and always went out of the way for us. I highly recommend this hotel. We had a great experience here. I booked directly with the hotel on their website and it was very quick and easy. I thought the value for the money was extremely good. 
