<Author>Vacations from Boston
<Content>Nice Modern Hotel, Great Location We just returned from an 8 night stay at the ME Madrid. We had a room overlooking the Plaza de Santa Ana on the 5th floor and had a small balcony as well. The only problem with the rooms overlooking the plaza is the noise into all hours of the night ... we did get use to it but on Thursday, Friday and Saturday nights ... the partying goes on all night long! But the view itself and the small balcony were nice to have ... and again we did end up getting use to the noise after the 1st night. Overall, the hotel staff was very helpful and spoke English well. They helped us with dinner reservations, cabs, etc. The area near the hotel provides many choices for restaurants ... we walked each night and tried different types of food each night. There was a very casual pizza place just off the square that a tour guide mentioned to us and we actually had dinner there on two nights for something casual and no reservation needed. At 9 PM the place was near empty but by 915 to 9:30 it was packed both nights we were there. Food was very good and right across the street was an ice cream shop ... so we could grab an ice cream and walk around the area after dinner. The location of the hotel is excellent for all the major sites ... we walked everywhere we wanted to go ... 5 minutes to the Puerto del Sol, less than 10 to the Plaza Mayor ... and the museums and Royal Palace all within walking distanct. We took two day side trips to Segovia and Toledo and used Le Tango (letango.com) for a personal 3 hour tour. We also reserved a 3 hour walking tour of Madrid on our first full day with Le Tango. They had been recommended on this site's forum and we were not disappointed! All the guides were informative, helpful and provided great information to help with other things to do, see after the 3 hours. We also used the Madrid Vision for two days ... it's the Madrid version of the hop on, hop off bus! It was a great way to get around and see different sites or areas.Overall, the hotel was very nice, very modern, comfortable bed and nice ammenities. It is expensive but overall I think worth it. We did have breakfast each morning in the hotel and it provided a good variety of hot and cold foods. 
